14/11/2010
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Local prosecutors have charged three former Bosnian Serb officers with committing war crimes against civilians, local media reported on Saturday (November 13th).
Goran Markovic, Ljubisa Vranjes and Mladen Milic allegedly killed two Croatian civilians and tried to kill another in Kotor Varos in July 1992.
(RTRS, Srna, BHRT, Fena, Dnevni Avaz - 13/11/10)
